SIMPLE: regulative
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Regulative
<hw>Reg"u*la*tive</hw> <pr>(r?g"?*l?*t?v)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Tending to regulate; regulating.</def>
<rj><au>Whewell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Metaph.)</fld> <def>Necessarily assumed by the mind
as fundamental to all other knowledge; furnishing fundamental
principles; <as>as, the <ex>regulative</ex> principles, or principles
<altname>a priori</altname>; the <ex>regulative</ex> faculty.</as></def>
<rj><au>Sir W. Hamilton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ These terms are borrowed from Kant, and suggest the
thought, allowed by Kant, that possibly these principles are only true
for the human mind, the operations and belief of which they
regulate.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Regulator</ent>⟦br⟧
